message.content:
An airliner is a large, commercial aircraft designed for transporting passengers or cargo. 
It typically has a narrow and elongated fuselage, with a high wing and multiple jet engines mounted below the wings. 
The exterior of an airliner is usually painted with the airline's livery or colors. 
It has a streamlined, aerodynamic shape to minimize drag and maximize fuel efficiency during flight. 
Airliners may feature multiple passenger cabins, restrooms, galleys, and storage areas for luggage and cargo. 
Common types of airliners include Boeing and Airbus models, which are used by airlines worldwide. 
Airliners are most commonly seen at airports, where they take off and land on runways and are serviced by ground crews.
